      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">My dear Sir Redmond ¶ I shall give the necessary instruction to the Curator of the Botanical Gardens to supply your gardener when he calls with what he wants. ¶ Alexander Elliott.annotation refers to ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">74.05.18</seg>
               <seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; "/>
            </p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">James Casey to Redmond Barry</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">UM312 Registrar's correspondence, 1874/19 Grounds, University of Melbourne Archives, Melbourne.</seg>
               <seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; "/>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; ">To proof.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>This letter was registered at the University on 19 May 1874, and it is dated to the preceding day.</p>
               </note>My dear Sir Redmond</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I shall give the necessary instruction to the Curator of the Botanical Gardens to supply your gardener when he calls with what he wants.</seg>
               <seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">Alexander Elliott</seg>.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; ">annotation refers to Elliott making an appt with Guilfoyle re plants.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; color: #C00000; ">Quote it?</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">_________</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>There will be a vote on the estimates (I hope) for the erection of a Botanical museum in the University Grounds. And it is proposed to transfer the admirable &amp; valuable collection gathered by Baron Von Mueller to the new building where the students of the University can have in common with the [general] public the advantage of inspecting the plants preserved in the herbarium. If you remember I had the honor of mentioning this matter to you some time since &amp; acting upon what I understood to be your wish I have prevailed upon the hon Chief Secretary to place a sum on the estimates for next year sufficient to erect a suitable building<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">The sum I have asked for is £2500. or £1000 more than Mr Wardell is sufficient</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">.</seg>
               <seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #C00000; ">I do not understand the reference to Wardell</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #C00000; ">.</seg>
                     </p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #C00000; ">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">Evidently Casey's request was not approved</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>by the Chief Secretary</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">, for in the debate on Supply in the Legislative Assembly, when the vote for the Government Botanist was considered, Casey referred to a future possibility when he said ' <space unit="chars" quantity="2"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">this colony possessed an herbarium of which it might well boast, for it was second to none in the world, and included a collection of preserved plants which, to those who could appreciate its value, was worth a very<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">considerable</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>sum of money. Perhaps it would be wise to consider, at the present moment, whether this herbarium ought not to be removed to the University, where it would be in proximity to those who desired to use it. Certainly if steps were taken with the view of placing it within the University grounds, in a suitable building, which would be available for university and also for popular uses, the matter would receive the favorable consideration of the Government' (Victoria<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont"
                             style="font-style: italic; color: #0070C0; ">Hansard</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">session 1874, vol. 20,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">pp. 2070-1)</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">.</seg>
                     </p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M apparently heard rumours<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">that</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>he was to be required to lecture at the University (see M to A. Brownless, 24 June 1874 (in this edition as 74-06-24a), which may have been a misunderstood reference to proposals to move the Herbarium.</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>M was never required to teach at the University nor was the Herbarium moved.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Would you let me know where it can be placed, and whether if the money be handed to the University authorities they would erect the building according to their own design — they guaranteeing the Government that the building would be suitable and available for the purpose and<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">accessable</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>at all reasonable times.</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">I have the honor to be</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>My dr Sir Redmond</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>J. J. Casey</seg>
            </p>
         </div>
      </body>
